This approach essentially creates a "code steal competition" where innovative miners are forced to expose their proprietary work, only to have it copied by others who didn't invest the time and resources into developing it.
Key issues I see:
- Removes competitive advantage for miners who invest heavily in R&D
- Creates perverse incentives where copying becomes more profitable than innovating
- Could lead to brain drain as serious developers leave for networks that protect IP
- May result in lower overall network quality as innovation decreases
